						<summary>

						<p>A slab lying in Survey No. 291, about (1/2) Kilometer to the north wall of the village.</p>						

						<p>17th century A.D.</p>						

						<p>This undated inscription can be assigned to 17th century on the basis of the palaeography.</p>						

						<p>The damaged and incomplete inscription seems to record the gift of a village and lands for the merit of some individual. It also mentions the village Vipunaganḍla.</p>						

						</summary>
